Divide by _8_, and round the value to the nearest _0.125_.

```java
x = Math.round(x / 8 / .125) * .125
```

Then, determine which _[eighths block](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Block_Elements#Character_table)_ to use.

```java
x -= Math.floor(x);
char c = (char) (0x258f - (x / .125));
```

Here is an example.

```java
String getHorizontal(double x) {
    x = Math.round(x / 8 / .125) * .125;
    String s = &quot;\u2588&quot;.repeat((int) Math.floor(x));
    x -= Math.floor(x);
    return s + (char) (0x258f - (x / .125));
}
```

