I recently had this exact same problem in a Kotlin based project that included a dependency on `kotlin-test-junit5`. I added a dependency on `junit-jupiter` version `5.9.1` and thought that this would bring in all other jUnit5 dependencies - it did not, because `kotlin-test-junit5` had already brought some older versions of some of the dependencies.

There are two solutions: either explicitly depend on `-api`, `-engine` and `-params` specifying the desired version, or specifying exlcusions on `kotlin-test-junit5`.

So instead of:
```xml
       &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.jetbrains.kotlin&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;kotlin-test-junit5&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;1.7.20&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-jupiter&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;5.9.1&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
```

Specify either:
```xml
   &lt;dependencyManagement&gt;
        &lt;!-- Use the JUnit BOM for version management --&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-bom&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;5.10.0&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;type&gt;pom&lt;/type&gt;
            &lt;scope&gt;import&lt;/scope&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
   &lt;/dependencyManagement&gt;

   &lt;dependencies&gt;
       ...
       &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.jetbrains.kotlin&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;kotlin-test-junit5&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;1.7.20&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-jupiter&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-jupiter-api&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-jupiter-engine&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-jupiter-params&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
        ...
    &lt;/dependencies&gt;
```

Or specify:

```xml
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-jupiter&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;5.9.1&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.jetbrains.kotlin&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;kotlin-test-junit5&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;1.7.20&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
            &lt;exclusions&gt;
                &lt;exclusion&gt;
                    &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/groupId&gt;
                    &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-jupiter-api&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                &lt;/exclusion&gt;
                &lt;exclusion&gt;
                    &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/groupId&gt;
                    &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-jupiter-engine&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                &lt;/exclusion&gt;
            &lt;/exclusions&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
```

Otherwise `junit-jupiter-api` and `junit-jupiter-engine` will be overridden to version 5.6.0 from `kotlin-test-junit5`.

Personally I find the second solution cleaner and easier to maintain but that&#39;s a matter of personal preference.

NB: In the first fix you could omit either the `junit-jupiter` parent dependency, or the explicit dependency on `junit-jupiter-params`, to save a few lines of XML. I know.

