# `java.time.LocalTime`

The java.time classes include `LocalTime` to represent a time-of-day only without a date and without a time zone.

&gt; So what I want is, 20:11:13 &lt; 01:00:00 &lt; 14:49:00.

First we define the boundaries. Your input strings happen to comply with standard [ISO 8601][1] formats. The java.time classes use ISO 8601 formats by default, so no need to specify a formatting pattern.

